comment.body:
In core modeling context, please use

```
ar translate = this._injector.get('translate', false) || function(s) { return s; };
```

In JSX / preact scopes, please use 

```
const translate = useService('translate');
```

In particular this library shall use the standard `translate` service, in the [core modeling way](https://github.com/bpmn-io/bpmn-js/search?p=2&q=translate).

issue.title: Copy and paste between different browser windows
issue.body:
__Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.__

As a user I want to copy and paste parts of my diagram between different browser/app windows.

Use case: Have multiple diagrams opened in different tabs, but also have diagrams opened in different bpmn-js based applications (Camunda Modeler, Camunda Web Modeler, bpmn.io demo).


__Describe the solution you'd like__

* [ ] If I copy parts of the diagram it is put into the system clipboard in a way that
* [ ] Pasting with the [canvas selected](https://github.com/bpmn-io/diagram-js/pull/659) pastes from the system clipboard, if it holds bpmn-js contents

__Describe alternatives you've considered__

None.


__Additional context__

The web platform provides clipboard API as well as `copy` events we may be able to hook into.

On the bpmn-js side we'd need to ensure our copy/paste implementation is side-effect free, and the copied tree is serializable.


----


Depends on https://github.com/bpmn-io/diagram-js/pull/659.

comment.body: We were not able to follow up on the required changes to make browser native focus handling + copy/paste available across all our toolkits (https://github.com/bpmn-io/internal-docs/issues/614#issuecomment-1220481826).

issue.title: Copy and paste between different browser windows
issue.body:
__Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.__

As a user I want to copy and paste parts of my diagram between different browser/app windows.

Use case: Have multiple diagrams opened in different tabs, but also have diagrams opened in different bpmn-js based applications (Camunda Modeler, Camunda Web Modeler, bpmn.io demo).


__Describe the solution you'd like__

* [ ] If I copy parts of the diagram it is put into the system clipboard in a way that
* [ ] Pasting with the [canvas selected](https://github.com/bpmn-io/diagram-js/pull/659) pastes from the system clipboard, if it holds bpmn-js contents

__Describe alternatives you've considered__

None.


__Additional context__

The web platform provides clipboard API as well as `copy` events we may be able to hook into.

On the bpmn-js side we'd need to ensure our copy/paste implementation is side-effect free, and the copied tree is serializable.


----


Depends on https://github.com/bpmn-io/diagram-js/pull/659.

comment.body: We were not able to follow up on the required changes to make browser native focus handling + copy/paste available across all our toolkits (https://github.com/bpmn-io/internal-docs/issues/614#issuecomment-1220481826).

In core modeling context, please use

```
ar translate = this._injector.get('translate', false) || function(s) { return s; };
```

In JSX / preact scopes, please use 

```
const translate = useService('translate');
```

In particular this library shall use the standard `translate` service, in the [core modeling way](https://github.com/bpmn-io/bpmn-js/search?p=2&q=translate).

issue.title: Copy and paste between different browser windows
issue.body:
__Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.__

As a user I want to copy and paste parts of my diagram between different browser/app windows.

Use case: Have multiple diagrams opened in different tabs, but also have diagrams opened in different bpmn-js based applications (Camunda Modeler, Camunda Web Modeler, bpmn.io demo).


__Describe the solution you'd like__

* [ ] If I copy parts of the diagram it is put into the system clipboard in a way that
* [ ] Pasting with the [canvas selected](https://github.com/bpmn-io/diagram-js/pull/659) pastes from the system clipboard, if it holds bpmn-js contents

__Describe alternatives you've considered__

None.


__Additional context__

The web platform provides clipboard API as well as `copy` events we may be able to hook into.

On the bpmn-js side we'd need to ensure our copy/paste implementation is side-effect free, and the copied tree is serializable.


----


Depends on https://github.com/bpmn-io/diagram-js/pull/659.

comment.body: We were not able to follow up on the required changes to make browser native focus handling + copy/paste available across all our toolkits (https://github.com/bpmn-io/internal-docs/issues/614#issuecomment-1220481826).
